      "edited_at": "2025-08-15T09:51:18.587Z",
      "content": "<p>\u2026DDIs, most importantly for the root disk itself. The dissection logic will only take partitions into account whose GPT partition name string matches that glob.</p><p>Or in other words, let&#39;s say you maintain your own private OS &quot;ToyOS&quot;. Just name all your partitions &quot;ToyOS_xyz&quot; (e.g. &quot;ToyOS_root&quot; or &quot;ToyOS_swap&quot; or so), and then use &quot;systemd.image_filter=ToyOS_*&quot; and the dissection logic will only take partitions into account that are actually associated with your OS.</p><p>Also note that all\u2026</p>",
